<s> FROM FASHION TO FUNDAMENTALS MORE AND MORE PUBLIC SCHOOL SYSTEMS ARE IMPOSING STRICT DRESS CODES </s>
<s> IT IS ARGUED UNIFORMS WILL HELP KEEP STUDENTS OUT OF TROUBLE AND PARENTS OUT OF DEBT BUT C. N. N.'S LISA PRICE REPORTS NOT EVERYONE'S BUYING THAT </s>
<s> IT'S A TOUGH WAY TO START THE SCHOOL YEAR </s>
<s> WE'RE LOOKING FOR CHILDREN WHO ARE ABSOLUTELY NOT IN UNIFORM </s>
<s> A STRICT NEW DRESS CODE IN EFFECT AT A CHICAGO SUBURBAN SCHOOL DISTRICT A PUBLIC SCHOOL DISTRICT GIVES SCHOOL ADMINISTRATORS THE AUTHORITY TO EXCLUDE THIS SECOND GRADER FROM ATTENDING CLASS </s>
<s> SEVEN YEAR OLD BRANDY WILL REMAIN SEPARATED FROM HER CLASS UNTIL SHE WEARS THE WHITE AND BLUE UNIFORM JUST LIKE EVERYONE ELSE </s>
<s> THE GIRL'S MOTHER IS PREPARED FOR A FIGHT </s>
<s> THEY ARE NOT UPHOLDING THE LAW </s>
<s> THEY ARE DEPRIVING MY CHILDREN OF THE RIGHT TO FREE EDUCATION </s>
<s> I'M A TAXPAYER I LIVE IN THE COMMUNITY MY CHILDREN HAVE A RIGHT TO A FREE EDUCATION </s>
<s> GIVEN OVERWHELMING APPROVAL TO INSTITUTE THE POLICY BY PARENTS AND ADMINISTRATORS THE SCHOOL SUPERINTENDENT HAS NO INTENTION OF BACKING DOWN </s>
<s> IT'S ABSOLUTELY MANDATORY WITH NO EXCEPTIONS OF ANY KIND </s>
<s> THE KIDS MUST WEAR WHITE TOPS NAVY BLUE BOTTOMS BLACK SHOES NO EXCEPTIONS FOR ANY REASON </s>
<s> MANY PARENTS IN THIS AND OTHER SCHOOL DISTRICTS AROUND THE COUNTRY LIKE THE IDEA OF A DRESS CODE NOT ONLY BECAUSE IT SAVES MONEY BUT BECAUSE IT DISCOURAGES GANG VIOLENCE WHICH CAN ERUPT WHEN GANG MEMBERS WEAR THE WRONG THING </s>
<s> LET'S SAY ONE COLOR ONE GANG COLOR IS BLUE AND THEN THE OTHER ONE IS RED AND THEN ONE IS COMING THIS WAY AND THE OTHER ONE'S COMING THAT WAY THEN THAT WOULD START A GANG PROBLEM </s>
<s> IN CALIFORNIA GOVERNOR PETE WILSON RECENTLY SIGNED INTO THE LAW THE COUNTRY'S FIRST LEGISLATION GIVING THE STATE SCHOOL BOARDS AUTHORITY TO ENACT DRESS CODE POLICIES </s>
<s> THE WRONG COMBINATION OF CLOTHES CAN GET YOU KILLED IN CERTAIN DISTRICTS </s>
<s> THE CALIFORNIA LAW NOT WITHSTANDING PUBLIC SCHOOLS WITH MANDATORY DRESS CODES MAY FACE LEGAL BATTLES AS THOSE DRESS CODES ARE CHALLENGED CONSTITUTIONALLY </s>
<s> POLICIES THAT PUNISH STUDENTS FOR NOT WEARING UNIFORMS OR DON'T ALLOW STUDENTS TO ATTEND SCHOOL IF THEY DON'T WEAR A UNIFORM VIOLATE THOSE FIRST AMENDMENT RIGHTS THAT EVERY SINGLE PUBLIC SCHOOL STUDENT HAS </s>
<s> BUT SUPERINTENDENT ED CHARTRAW DOESN'T BELIEVE HIS SUBURBAN CHICAGO SCHOOL DISTRICT IS WALKING ON SHAKY LEGAL GROUND </s>
<s> IF I WAS CONCERNED WE WOULDN'T HAVE A MANDATORY POLICY </s>
<s> THIS CHILD'S MOTHER HAS HOWEVER ALREADY FILED A COMPLAINT AND THE AMERICAN CIVIL LIBERTIES UNION EXPECTS IT TO BE ONE AMONG THOUSANDS FILED BY PARENTS WHO OPPOSE DRESS CODES IN SCHOOL DISTRICTS NATIONWIDE </s>
