<s> FRESH ECHOES OF A DEADLY ACCIDENT OVER IRAQ LAST APRIL </s>
<s> ONE THAT SAW UNITED STATES WAR PLANES DESTROY TWO U. S. HELICOPTERS </s>
<s> NOW SOME OF THE CREW OF AN AIRBORN RADAR PLANE THAT MONITORED THAT FRIENDLY FIRE DISASTER MAY BE HEADED TOWARD A MILITARY TRIAL </s>
<s> THE LATEST NOW FROM C. N. N.'S MILITARY AFFAIRS CORRESPONDENT JAMIE MCINTYRE HE'S AT THE PENTAGON </s>
<s> JAMIE </s>
<s> THAT'S RIGHT NATALIE SOURCES TELL C. N. N. THAT AN AIR FORCE BOARD OF OFFICERS ASSESSING BLAME FOR THE DOWNING OF TWO AMERICAN HELICOPTERS OVER IRAQ HAS MADE A PRELIMINARY RECOMMENDATION THAT SOME CREW MEMBERS OF AN AWACS CONTROL PLANE SHOULD BE COURT MARTIALED FOR DERELICTION OF DUTY </s>
<s> AN INVESTIGATION LAST MONTH FOUND A SERIES OF FATAL MISTAKES CAUSED THE APRIL FOURTEENTH FRIENDLY FIRE INCIDENT BUT DEFENSE SECRETARY WILLIAM PERRY SAID AT THE TIME THAT THE FAILURE OF THE AWACS CREW WAS MOST GLARING </s>
<s> KEY TO THAT IS AWACS </s>
<s> HAD AWACS BEEN OPERATING PROPERLY THERE WOULD NOT HAVE BEEN THE REMOTEST CHANCE OF THIS OPERATION HAPPENING </s>
<s> TWENTY SIX DIED WHEN THE U. S. ARMY BLACKHAWKS WERE SHOT DOWN BY TWO U. S. AIR FORCE F. FIFTEENS </s>
<s> A THREE MONTH INVESTIGATION FOUND THE ARMY BLACKHAWK PILOTS USED THE WRONG CODE IN THEIR INTERNATIONAL FRIEND OR FOE TRANSPONDER </s>
<s> THE F. FIFTEENS WERE FLYING TOO FAST TO MAKE PROPER IDENTIFICATION AND THE PILOTS WERE POORLY TRAINED IN HELICOPTER RECOGNITION </s>
<s> AND THAT THE AWACS CREW LOST TRACK OF THE HELICOPTERS AND WHEN THEY REAPPEARED ON A TRACKING SCOPE FAILED TO ALERT THE F. FIFTEENS </s>
<s> THERE WERE A SHOCKING NUMBER OF INSTANCES WHERE INDIVIDUALS FAILED TO DO THEIR JOBS PROPERLY </s>
<s> SOURCES SAY THE F. FIFTEEN PILOTS COULD ALSO FACE DISCIPLINE BUT THAT THE DISCIPLINE MIGHT BE LESS THAN COURT MARTIAL SINCE THE PILOTS WERE FOLLOWING THEIR RULES OF ENGAGEMENT </s>
<s> THE BOARD'S RECOMMENDATION IN THE CASE OF THE AWACS CREW IS NOT THE FINAL WORD </s>
<s> AN AIR FORCE GENERAL COULD OVERRULE THE BOARDS DECISION BUT GIVEN THE SERIOUSNESS OF THE MISTAKE MILITARY SOURCES SAY THAT IS UNLIKELY </s>
