<s> A GROWING TREND IN THE MEDICAL PROFESSION IS GIVING MANY PREGNANT WOMEN ONE LESS WORRY </s>
<s> C. N. N.'S NORMA QUARLES REPORTS MIDWIVES ARE DELIVERING MORE BABIES AND BRINGING MANY EXPECTING PARENTS PEACE OF MIND </s>
<s> HAVING A BABY CAN BE FRIGHTENING WITH MANY UNANSWERED QUESTIONS </s>
<s> EXPECTANT MOTHERS LIKE TRACY RUSSEK ARE INCREASINGLY SEEKING THE KIND OF PERSONALIZED CARE THEY CAN GET FROM NURSE MIDWIVES </s>
<s> SHEILA TAYLOR IS ONE OF THE NATION'S FOUR THOUSAND CERTIFIED NURSE MIDWIVES A REGISTERED NURSE WITH AN ADVANCED DEGREE IN MIDWIFERY </s>
<s> SHE'S PART OF DOCTOR LAWRENCE LEVITAN'S OB \ GYN STAFF </s>
<s> WE TALK TO THE PATIENT WE HEAR HER FEARS AND HER ANXIETIES AND WE'RE THERE ALL THE TIME </s>
<s> WELL I TRY TO GET THERE AS SOON AS POSSIBLE WHEN A PATIENT IS IN LABOR </s>
<s> NOT ALWAYS AVAILABLE FOR EVERY MOMENT </s>
<s> A COLLABORATION BETWEEN MIDWIVES AND PHYSICIANS IS A GROWING TREND FOR A NUMBER OF REASONS </s>
<s> IT'S MORE ECONOMICAL FOR A DOCTOR TO STAFF WITH MIDWIVES THAN TO HIRE OTHER DOCTORS </s>
<s> MIDWIVES USUALLY HANDLE THE NORMAL DELIVERIES LEAVING THE PROBLEM OR MORE DIFFICULT CASES TO THE PHYSICIANS </s>
<s> THERE'S CERTAINLY PARTS OF THE MEDICAL COMMUNITY WHO DON'T UNDERSTAND WHO NURSE MIDWIVES ARE WHO FEEL THREATENED I THINK BY OUR GROWTH WHO ARE NOT SUPPORTIVE </s>
<s> YOU HAVE TO ASK THE QUESTION WHAT'S THE POTENTIAL BACK UP </s>
<s> WHAT IF THERE IS AN EMERGENCY </s>
<s> WHAT IF THERE IS AN EMERGENCY </s>
<s> MOST NURSE MIDWIVES HAVE PHYSICIANS ON CALL AS A BACK UP IN CASE OF EMERGENCIES </s>
<s> IN THE LAST FIVE YEARS THE NUMBER OF BIRTHS ATTENDED BY NURSE MIDWIVES HAS INCREASED FROM LESS THAN THREE PERCENT TO ALMOST FIVE PERCENT IN THE UNITED STATES </s>
