<s> RESEARCHERS ARE NOW FOLLOWING UP SOME INTRIGUING FINDINGS IN THE FIGHT AGAINST ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE </s>
<s> IT APPEARS DRUGS COMMONLY USED TO TREAT ARTHRITIS MAY BE LINKED WITH DELAYING ALZHEIMER'S </s>
<s> C. N. N.'S ANDREW HOLTZ REPORTS </s>
<s> PEOPLE WITH ARTHRITIS OFTEN TAKE DRUGS INCLUDING STEROIDS IBUPROFEN ASPIRIN AND SIMILAR MEDICINES TO REDUCE INFLAMMATION </s>
<s> SOME OF THEM MAY ALSO BE DELAYING THE DEVELOPMENT OF ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE </s>
<s> RESEARCHERS AT DUKE UNIVERSITY STUDIED PAIRS OF TWIN BROTHERS IN WHICH ONE BROTHER HAS ALZHEIMER'S AND THE OTHER DOES NOT </s>
<s> SINCE IDENTICAL TWINS HAVE IDENTICAL GENES RESEARCHERS LOOKED FOR DIFFERENCES IN THEIR ENVIRONMENT OR EXPERIENCES </s>
<s> THE STATISTICS POINTED TO ANTIINFLAMMATORY DRUG THERAPY </s>
<s> PEOPLE WHO TAKE THESE TREATMENTS OFTEN GET THE DISEASE LATER THAN WOULD THEIR BROTHER </s>
<s> THE RESEARCHERS THEN LOOKED AT THE PATTERN OF ALZHEIMER'S IN SIBLINGS WHO ARE NOT TWINS </s>
<s> YOU CAN USE THIS KIND OF METHOD VERY MUCH THE WAY WE'D USE THE TWINS METHOD TO LOOK FOR ENVIRONMENT FACTORS </s>
<s> AGAIN THOSE WHO HAD LONG TERM TREATMENT WITH ANTIINFLAMMATORY DRUGS APPEAR TO DEVELOP ALZHEIMER'S LATER IF AT ALL </s>
<s> OUR FINDINGS SUGGEST THAT USING THESE MEDICINES IN MIDDLE LIFE OR AN EARLY OLD AGE MAY STAVE OFF THE ONSET OF THE SYMPTOMS ALL TOGETHER </s>
<s> THE STATISTICAL LENGTH MATCHES SOME LABORATORY FINDINGS </s>
<s> THINGS THAT ARE AKIN TO INFLAMMATION SEEM TO BE GOING ON IN AND AROUND THE LESIONS IN ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE AND YOU CAN SEE THIS UNDER THE MICROSCOPE </s>
<s> DOCTORS WARN THESE DRUGS CAN CAUSE BLEEDING AND OTHER SIDE EFFECTS </s>
<s> SO FAR THERE HAVE BEEN ONLY PRELIMINARY STUDIES IN A FEW ALZHEIMER'S PATIENTS YET THE ANTIINFLAMMATORY LEAD IS ONE RESEARCHERS ARE EAGER TO FOLLOW UP </s>
<s> WE DON'T BELIEVE THAT THE INFLAMMATORY REACTION IS PRIMARY </s>
<s> IT'S NOT CAUSING THE DISEASE BUT IT MAY BE CONTRIBUTING TO THE LOSS OF NEURONS </s>
<s> IF WE COULD COMBAT THAT WE MAY ABLE TO SLOW THE RATE OF DECLINE </s>
<s> THERE ARE OTHER LEADS </s>
<s> STATISTICS ALSO SUGGEST WOMEN WHO TAKE ESTROGEN ARE LESS LIKELY TO DEVELOP ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE </s>
<s> AND HIGHER EDUCATION AND INTELLECTUALLY DEMANDING CAREERS MAY OFFER SOME PROTECTION </s>
<s> IT MAY NOT ALTER THE COURSE OF THE DISEASE BUT IT CHANGES THE EXPRESSION OF THE DISEASE </s>
<s> IT'S SOMETHING LIKE HAVING RESERVED CAPACITY </s>
<s> RESEARCHER MAY ALSO SOON BE TESTING NICOTINE PATCHES ON PEOPLE WITH ALZHEIMER'S </s>
<s> THE PSYCHOACTIVE INGREDIENT OF CIGARETTES BOOSTS THE PERFORMANCE OF MICE ON MEMORY TEST </s>
<s> THE RESEARCHERS STRESS THEY'RE TESTING NICOTINE PATCHES </s>
<s> THEY DON'T WANT PEOPLE WITH ALZHEIMER'S TO TAKE UP SMOKING </s>
<s> ANDREW HOLTZ C. N. N. </s>
