<s> WELL THE MURDER OF A ROMAN CATHOLIC PRIEST IN HAITI IS FUELING U. S. RESOLVES TO GET RESOLVE TO GET RID OF HAITI'S MILITARY REGIME </s>
<s> SUNDAY'S ASSASSINATION OF JEAN MARIE VINCENT IS CHILLING EVIDENCE THE CLERICAL COLLAR IS NO PROTECTION FROM HAITI'S POLITICAL VIOLENCE </s>
<s> C. N. N.'S PETER ARNETT LOOKS AT THE PRIEST'S LIFE AND DEATH </s>
<s> IN LIFE FATHER JEAN MARIE VINCENT WAS A SYMBOL OF HOPE FOR HAITI'S MILLIONS OF PEASANTS </s>
<s> A GRASS ROOTS REFORMER WHOSE STRONG ADVOCACY OF DEMOCRACY MADE HIM A TARGET OF VIOLENCE </s>
<s> THE VIOLENCE THAT HAD FOLLOWED HIM FOR NEARLY A DECADE FINALLY COST HIM HIS LIFE WHEN THE FORTY NINE YEAR OLD PRIEST WAS GUNNED DOWN OUTSIDE A CHURCH IN THE HAITIAN CAPITAL OF PORT AU PRINCE </s>
<s> HIS COLLEAGUES IMMEDIATELY ACCUSED THE MILITARY LED HAITIAN GOVERNMENT OF COMPLICITY IN THE MURDER </s>
<s> THIS IS STICK TERROR A CAMPAIGN OF HEAVY INTIMIDATION </s>
<s> HAITI'S SENIOR MILITARY COMMANDER GENERAL RAOUL CEDRAS WAS ASKED ABOUT THE KILLING DURING A PUBLIC APPEARANCE SOUTH OF THE CAPITOL </s>
<s> HE DENIED ANY KNOWLEDGE OF THE CIRCUMSTANCES </s>
<s> WHEN YOU HAVE A REGRETTABLE INCIDENT SUCH AS WHICH HAPPENED LAST NIGHT YOU HAVE TO HAVE ALL THE FACTS IN BEFORE YOU COMMENT </s>
<s> BUT A U. S. EMBASSY OFFICIAL IN PORT AU PRINCE ALSO POINTED THE FINGER AT THE HAITIAN AUTHORITIES </s>
<s> I THINK IT'S A VERY SAD AND TRAGIC REFLECTION ON THE CURRENT STATE OF OPPRESSION IN THIS COUNTRY </s>
<s> FATHER VINCENT WAS BEST KNOWN AS THE LEADER OF THE LAND REFORM MOVEMENT IN NORTHWEST HAITI THAT DREW THE ANGER OF LAND OWNERS AND LED TO THE MASSACRE OF SEVERAL HUNDRED PEASANTS IN JULY NINETEEN EIGHTY SEVEN </s>
<s> THE PRIEST WAS ALSO KNOWN FOR HIS CLOSE ASSOCIATION WITH EXILED PRESIDENT JEAN BERTRAND ARISTIDE AND WAS INJURED WHILE SAVING ARISTIDE'S LIFE IN AN ATTACK BY THUGS DURING A NINETEEN EIGHTY SEVEN ELECTION CAMPAIGN </s>
<s> THE ASSASSINATION OF FATHER VINCENT IS THE FIRST OF A PRIEST SINCE THE HAITIAN MILITARY SEIZED POWER IN A NINETEEN NINETY ONE COUP D'ETAT AND IS AN ACT THAT CATHOLIC COLLEAGUES FEAR BREAKS A TABOO ON THE MURDER OF RELIGIOUS FIGURES </s>
<s> THE KILLING OF FATHER VINCENT COMES AT A TIME WHEN THE HAITIAN AUTHORITIES ARE SHOWING MORE CONFIDENCE IN THEMSELVES </s>
<s> WITH GENERAL CEDRAS COURTING THE PUBLIC IN FREQUENT CAMPAIGN STYLE APPEARANCES AND MILITARY AND POLICE SHOWING THE FLAG IN PARADES THROUGH THE CAPITOL </s>
<s> IT IS CLEAR THAT HAITIAN AUTHORITIES REMAIN IN OPEN DEFIANCE OF U. S. POLICY AND EVEN THOUGH DENUNCIATIONS OF FATHER VINCENT'S MURDER CAME FROM THE U. S. SECRETARY OF STATE HIMSELF THOSE LIVING IN FEAR IN HAITI ARE STILL WAITING TO SEE IF ACTIONS EVENTUALLY WILL SPEAK LOUDER THAN WORDS </s>
<s> PETER ARNETT C. N. N. PORT AU PRINCE </s>
