<s> FOR VETERANS OF PAST HEALTH CARE REFORM STRUGGLES IN WASHINGTON PRESIDENT CLINTON'S EFFORT HAS BEEN A DEPRESSING DEJA VU </s>
<s> I WAS ABLE MANY MONTHS AGO TO KIND OF SKETCH OUT WHAT YOU WOULD SEE HAPPEN WHEN THIS DEBATE GOT JOINED </s>
<s> DOCTOR JAMES MONGEN IS THE DIRECTOR OF THE TRUMAN MEDICAL CENTER IN KANSAS CITY </s>
<s> IN THE SEVENTIES AND EIGHTIES HE WORKED ON BOTH PRESIDENT NIXON AND PRESIDENT CARTER'S EFFORTS TO PASS COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH REFORM </s>
<s> JUST BECAUSE YOU KNOW THERE'S GOING TO BE A TRAIN WRECK DOESN'T MAKE IT ANY MORE PLEASANT TO WATCH THE TRAIN WRECK </s>
<s> BASED ON HIS PAST EXPERIENCE MONGEN DEVELOPED A CHART HE CALLS THE SLIPPERY SLOPE TO UNIVERSAL COVERAGE </s>
<s> IT SHOWS STEP BY STEP HOW PAST EFFORTS AT HEALTH REFORM FAILED </s>
<s> THIS YEAR'S EFFORT BY THE CLINTON ADMINISTRATION FOLLOWED MONGEN'S CHART EXACTLY </s>
<s> THE PROCESS BEGINS WITH A PROPOSAL FOR AN EMPLOYER MANDATE </s>
<s> THEN IN AN EFFORT TO ACCOMMODATE THE OPPOSITION THE MANDATE IS PHASED IN </s>
<s> THEN CERTAIN EMPLOYERS ARE EXEMPTED </s>
<s> THEN THE EMPLOYER MANDATE IS DROPPED ALTOGETHER AND AN INDIVIDUAL MANDATE IS FOUND TO BE TOO EXPENSIVE TO SUBSIDIZE </s>
<s> THEN THE DEBATE ARRIVES AT THE POINT WHERE MONGEN FEARS IT IS TODAY </s>
<s> AND THEN AT THE FINAL STEP AT THE BOTTOM OF CHART IS JUST TO ESTABLISH AN EMPTY GOAL THAT WE'LL HAVE UNIVERSAL COVERAGE IN SAY THE YEAR TWO THOUSAND </s>
<s> THAT'S A ROUND NUMBER AND SIMILAR TO WHAT WE DID WITH FULL EMPLOYMENT AND HUMPHREY HAWKINS AND BALANCED BUDGETS AND GRAMM RUDMAN </s>
<s> MONGEN PREDICTS THAT UNIVERSAL COVERAGE WILL JOIN A BALANCED BUDGET AND FULL EMPLOYMENT GOALS THAT ARE ENSHRINED IN LEGISLATION BUT NEVER ACHIEVED </s>
<s> BUT UNLIKE FULL EMPLOYMENT OR A BALANCED BUDGET UNIVERSAL COVERAGE WAS THE SUBJECT OF A MEMORABLE ACT OF POLITICAL THEATER </s>
<s> IF YOU SEND ME LEGISLATION THAT DOES NOT GUARANTEE EVERY AMERICAN PRIVATE HEALTH INSURANCE THAT CAN NEVER BE TAKEN AWAY YOU WILL FORCE ME TO TAKE THIS PEN VETO THE LEGISLATION AND WE'LL COME RIGHT BACK HERE AND START ALL OVER AGAIN </s>
<s> REGARDLESS OF HOW THE HEALTH CARE REFORM DEBATE PLAYS OUT THIS FALL THE PICTURE OF PRESIDENT CLINTON WAVING HIS PEN IN THE AIR IS BOUND TO BE REPLAYED AGAIN AND AGAIN </s>
<s> WHITE HOUSE OFFICIALS ARE WONDERING WHETHER THE REMINDERS WILL HAVE THE SAME EFFECT AS THE RERUNS OF ANOTHER FAMOUS PRESIDENTIAL PLEDGE </s>
<s> READ MY LIPS NO NEW TAXES </s>
<s> BREAKING A SPECIFIC AND DRAMATIC PROMISE LIKE NO NEW TAXES IS NEVER A GOOD IDEA FOR A POLITICIAN </s>
<s> BUT EVEN REPUBLICAN STRATEGISTS SUCH AS POLLSTER FRANK LUNTZ SAY PRESIDENT CLINTON WON'T SUFFER AS MUCH AS PRESIDENT BUSH DID </s>
