<s> AT THE WHITE HOUSE I'M MARA LIASSON </s>
<s> WE HEAR THIS MUSIC AND WE THINK LITTLE RASCALS THOSE DEAD END KIDS ROLLING DOWN BIG HILLS IN TINY SOAPBOX RACING CARS </s>
<s> THIS SONG THE GOOD OLD DAYS WAS WRITTEN BY LEROY SHIELD </s>
<s> HE COMPOSED HUNDREDS OF TINY SONGS FOR THE HAL ROACH COMEDY STUDIOS BACK IN THE NINETEEN THIRTIES </s>
<s> HIS MUSIC PROVIDED THE COLOR FOR THE BLACK AND WHITE FILMS OF STAN LAUREL AND OLIVER HARDY </s>
<s> SHIELD WAS RARELY CREDITED FOR COMPOSING THESE SONGS AND LEFT NO WRITTEN SCORES </s>
<s> THAT'S WHERE OUR STORY BEGINS WITH TWO BOYS GROWING UP IN HOLLAND </s>
<s> GERT JAN BLOM NOW AN ORCHESTRA LEADER AND PIET SCHROEDERS STILL A FANATIC </s>
<s> WE ALL GREW UP WATCHING NOT SO MUCH LITTLE RASCALS BUT WE ALL WATCHED LAUREL AND HARDY ON T. V. AND SOME TIME IN THE MID EIGHTIES I BECAME RATHER OBSESSED BY IT </s>
<s> THEN I ASKED AN ENGINEER IF IT WOULD BE POSSIBLE TO SPLICE SOME DIFFERENT BITS OF SOUNDTRACK TOGETHER SO YOU WOULD GET ONE COMPLETE PIECE AND THIS WAS POSSIBLE BECAUSE THEY RE USED ALL THOSE TRACKS OVER AND OVER AGAIN </s>
<s> I GAVE THOSE TAPES TO GERT JAN WHO WAS A MUSICIAN AND ORCHESTRA LEADER AND I SAID TO HIM THIS IS GREAT MUSIC THIS IS THE BEST MUSIC EVER RECORDED IN THE TWENTIETH CENTURY </s>
<s> WHY DON'T YOU TRY AND ORGANIZE A BAND WHO CAN PLAY THAT </s>
<s> THE MOMENT THAT PIET STARTED THROWING THESE TAPES IN MY MAILBOX I WOULD HEAR THIS MUSIC AND IT WOULD BE INSTANTLY LINKED WITH THOSE FILMS </s>
<s> LEROY SHIELD WAS A GREAT CRAFTSMAN </s>
<s> HE STARTED OUT AS A CLASSICAL PIANIST PLAYING RAVEL AND STRAVINSKY AND SCHOENBERG </s>
<s> THEN HE STARTED WORKING IN THIS SMALL IDIOM THESE MOOD PIECES ROMANTIC PIECES ANXIETY PIECES </s>
<s> IT IS LIKE A HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPION DOING A LIGHTWEIGHT MATCH OR SOMETHING </s>
<s> THIS TUNE IS CALLED BEAUTIFUL LADY AND IT'S BASICALLY USED WHENEVER A BEAUTIFUL LADY IS VISIBLE IN THE FILMS </s>
<s> SOMETIMES IT'S ALSO USED IN A CYNICAL WAY LIKE WHEN OLIVER HARDY SHOWS STAN LAUREL A PICTURE OF HIS FAT AND UGLY WIFE YOU WOULD HEAR BEAUTIFUL LADY SO THIS OPTIMISTIC AND FRIVOLOUS PIECE THEN ADDS A CERTAIN CYNICISM TO THAT PARTICULAR SCENE </s>
<s> THE INSTRUMENTATION IS BASICALLY A SHIELD SET UP LIKE THREE SAXOPHONES TWO TRUMPETS TROMBONE TWO VIOLINS A CELLO GUITAR OR BANJO BASS PIANO AND PERCUSSION VERY LIGHT DRUMS </s>
<s> YOU WILL NEVER HEAR LOUD DRUMS IN SHIELD'S MUSIC </s>
<s> WE SET OUT TO NOT ONLY RECONSTRUCT MR. SHIELD'S COMPOSITIONS WE ALSO FELT IT WOULD BE GOOD TO TRY AND APPROACH THIS LOW FIDELITY YOU KNOW THE SPECIFIC SOUND THAT YOU HEAR IN THOSE FILMS WHICH WAS BASICALLY A ONE MIC RECORDING </s>
<s> MUSICIANS IN THE THIRTIES WOULD BE VERY GOOD IN PLAYING DYNAMIC </s>
<s> SO WHEN A VIOLIN HAS THE LEAD PART THE TRUMPET PLAYER WHO HAS A BACKGROUND PART SHOULD PLAY HIS PART SO QUIETLY THAT THE VIOLIN IS AT THAT POINT THE LOUDEST INSTRUMENT </s>
<s> ANOTHER THING THAT CONTRIBUTED TO THE SOUND QUALITY IS THE FACT THAT ALL THE SAXOPHONES AND ALL THE TRUMPETS ARE PERIOD INSTRUMENTS </s>
<s> THESE INSTRUMENTS HAVE A VERY DIFFERENT SOUND FROM AN INSTRUMENT THAT'S MADE LET'S SAY SOMEWHERE IN THE NINETEEN EIGHTIES </s>
<s> THE INSTRUMENTS THEY USED WERE HEAVIER </s>
<s> THE MOUTH PIECES THEY USED WERE MADE OF BAKELITE AND THEY USED VERY THICK REEDS SO THAT THE QUALITY OF THE TONE THAT THEY PRODUCED HAD MUCH MORE WARMTH </s>
<s> ANOTHER THING IS THAT MUSICIANS IN THOSE DAYS REALLY KNEW HOW TO PLAY WITH A MICROPHONE YOU KNOW </s>
<s> MUSICIANS THEN CONSIDERED THE RECORDING MIC AS MUCH AS AN INSTRUMENT AS THE INSTRUMENT THAT THEY PLAYED </s>
<s> SO WHEN THEY GOT INTO THE STUDIO THEY WERE EXPERIMENTING WITH HANGING PIECES OF CLOTH OVER THE HORN OF THE SAXOPHONES TOGETHER A BEAUTIFUL MELLOW SOUND OR THE TRUMPET PLAYER WOULD BLOW AWAY FROM THE MICROPHONE TO CREATE A MORE DISTANT SOUND </s>
<s> SO IN A WAY EVERY MUSICIAN IN THE BAND WAS MIXING WAS PRODUCING THE ALBUM </s>
<s> I GUESS THAT'S WHAT GOT INTO THE RECORDINGS THAT'S WHAT I HEAR WHEN I LISTEN TO THEM </s>
<s> NOW I THINK ONE OF THE BEST EXAMPLES OF THAT MELLOW TONE IS A TRACK CALLED RIDING ALONG </s>
<s> WHEN THE RECORDING WAS FINISHED AND WE HAD FINALLY A DAT TAPE I WENT INTO THE MASTERING ROOM TO CUT THE FINAL TAPE FROM WHICH THE C. D.S ARE MADE AND THE TECHNICIAN THAT I WORKED WITH IN THIS ROOM KNEW NOTHING OF THE PROJECT I WAS JUST HIS THIRD CUSTOMER FOR THAT DAY </s>
<s> SO I COME IN WITH THE TAPE AND HE PUT IT ON AND WE WERE LISTENING TO THE THIRD TRACK ON THE TAPE </s>
<s> HE SAID IN A VERY CASUAL WAY HE SAID I ALWAYS LIKED THE SOUND OF THOSE FORTIES RECORDING </s>
<s> THE SOUND OF THE INSTRUMENTS IS ALWAYS SO BEAUTIFUL </s>
<s> I SAID WELL THIS WAS RECORDED THE DAY BEFORE YESTERDAY AND HE COULDN'T BELIEVE THAT </s>
<s> THAT WAS A GREAT COMPLIMENT </s>
<s> GERT JAN BLOM OF THE BEAU HUNKS ORCHESTRA ALONG WITH AUDIO RECONSTRUCTIONIST PIET SCHROEDERS </s>
<s> THE C. D. IS CALLED THE BEAU HUNKS PLAY THE ORIGINAL LITTLE RASCALS MUSIC </s>
