<s> MORE THAN SEVEN HUNDRED CUBANS WERE PICKED UP BY THE COAST GUARD TODAY IN THE STRAITS OF FLORIDA </s>
<s> THEY WILL JOIN SOME FIFTEEN THOUSAND OTHERS BEING DETAINED AT THE GUANTANAMO NAVAL BASE ON THE ISLAND'S SOUTHEASTERN CORNER </s>
<s> NPR'S ANCEL MARTINEZ TRAVELED TO THE BASE TODAY AND HE VISITED THE NEWLY EXPANDED CUBAN REFUGEE CAMPS THERE </s>
<s> THEY'RE HOUSED IN CANVAS TENTS AND THEIR LIVING SPACE IS BASICALLY A CANVAS ALUMINUM COT </s>
<s> THEY'RE LINED ABOUT FORTY LONG AND ABOUT THREE WIDE </s>
<s> THEY DON'T HAVE A LOT OF SPACE TO LIVE IN BUT THE YARD IS CLEAN THEY CAN HAVE SOME GRASS AREA BUT THE SUN IS VERY HOT SO YOU DON'T WANT TO STAY OUT IN THE YARD THAT LONG </s>
<s> AROUND THE PERIMETER IS A CONCERTINA WIRE AND BEYOND THAT ARE THE M. P.S WHO ARE TRYING TO BE OF SOME ASSISTANCE BUT MOST OF THEM DON'T SPEAK SPANISH </s>
<s> SO THE PEOPLE WHO DO SPEAK ENGLISH IN THE YARD OR THE BARRACKS WHERE THE REFUGEES ARE HOUSED THEY BECOME THE GO BETWEEN BETWEEN THE REFUGEES AND THE MILITARY PERSONNEL </s>
<s> AND WHAT SORT OF FOOD DO THEY HAVE AND WHERE DO THEY EAT </s>
<s> THE FOOD THEY HAVE ARE HUMANITARIAN DAILY RATIONS FROM THE UNITED STATES AND THEY GO DOWN TO A CENTRAL POINT AND JUST PICK THEM UP AND THEY'LL EAT THEM BACK AT THEIR COTS </s>
<s> THERE IS NOT REALLY A MESS HALL </s>
<s> ONLY A FEW OF THE CAMPS REALLY HAVE RUNNING WATER SO IT'S MOSTLY BOTTLED WATER THAT'S BEING BROUGHT IN </s>
<s> THEIR TOILET FACILITIES ARE SIMPLE PORT A JOHNS OR PORT A POTTIES AND THEY DON'T HAVE SOAP AND THEY DON'T HAVE PLACES TO WASH THEIR CLOTHES THAT MUCH AND OF COURSE AFTER THEIR JOURNEYS ON A RAFT THEY WOULD LIKE SOME TYPE OF CLEANLINESS </s>
<s> ANCEL WHEN YOU GO INTO A SITUATION LIKE THAT YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY ESCORTED BY MILITARY PERSONNEL </s>
<s> DO YOU FEEL THAT YOU HAD A GOOD LOOK AT THE ENTIRE CUBAN SITUATION THERE AT GUANTANAMO </s>
<s> YES </s>
