<s> NPR'S ANCEL MARTINEZ TALKING WITH US FROM GUANTANAMO NAVAL BASE IN CUBA </s>
<s> ONE OF PRESIDENT CLINTON'S TOP PRIORITIES CAMPAIGN FINANCE REFORM HAS BEEN STALLED IN CONGRESS FOR MONTHS NOW BUT THROUGHOUT THE DEBATE ONE GROUP HAS BEEN LARGELY IGNORED THE FEDERAL ELECTION COMMISSION WHICH WILL HAVE TO MAKE THE NEW RULES WORK </s>
<s> THAT'S NOT SURPRISING SAY PEOPLE BOTH INSIDE AND OUTSIDE CONGRESS BECAUSE FOR YEARS THE F. E. C. HAS BEEN THOUGHT TO BE INEFFECTIVE HAMSTRUNG BY LACK OF MONEY LIMITED POWERS AND A CUMBERSOME STRUCTURE </s>
<s> IN PART ONE OF A TWO PART SERIES NPR'S PETER KENYON REPORTS THERE ARE SIGNS OF LIFE AT THE F. E. C. BUT THE AGENCY'S AGGRESSIVE NEW ATTITUDE HAS PROMPTED SOME IN CONGRESS TO CONSIDER CUTTING THE COMMISSION'S ALREADY MODEST BUDGET </s>
<s> ON AUGUST THIRD REPORTERS GATHERED AT THE FEDERAL ELECTION COMMISSION BUILDING IN WASHINGTON FOR A RARE EVENT IN FACT THE FIRST OF ITS KIND AN F. E. C. NEWS CONFERENCE TO ANNOUNCE PENALTIES FOR ILLEGAL CAMPAIGN CONTRIBUTIONS </s>
<s> WE APPRECIATE YOUR COMING THIS MORNING </s>
<s> AS YOU KNOW THE FEDERAL ELECTION COMMISSION ONLY HOLDS THESE SORTS OF PRESS CONFERENCES WHEN WE HAVE SOMETHING UNUSUALLY IMPORTANT TO ANNOUNCE WHICH WE BELIEVE WE HAVE TODAY </s>
<s> WHAT F. E. C. CHAIRMAN TREVOR POTTER HAD TO ANNOUNCE WERE FINES OF MORE THAN ONE HUNDRED SIXTY THOUSAND DOLLARS AGAINST MOSTLY JAPANESE OWNED COMPANIES WHICH HAD DONATED TO STATE AND LOCAL ELECTIONS IN HAWAII </s>
<s> FOREIGN DONATIONS TO U. S. CAMPAIGNS ARE ILLEGAL </s>
<s> IT WAS THE LARGEST ENFORCEMENT ACTION EVER TAKEN BY THE F. E. C. AGAINST FOREIGN CONTRIBUTORS </s>
<s> THE NEWS CONFERENCE DID TWO THINGS IT HIGHLIGHTED THE SUCCESSFUL CONCLUSION OF A COMPLEX FIVE YEAR INVESTIGATION AND SERVED NOTICE THAT THE F. E. C. WAS PREPARED TO CRACK DOWN ON THESE TYPES OF VIOLATIONS </s>
<s> WHAT IT DIDN'T DO WAS OFFER MUCH RELIEF TO THE OPPOSITION CANDIDATES WHO HAD FILED THE ORIGINAL COMPLAINTS BACK IN NINETEEN EIGHTY NINE </s>
<s> NOT ONLY WERE THE ELECTIONS IN QUESTION OVER BUT THE TERMS OF MOST OF THE WINNERS HAD EXPIRED </s>
<s> EVEN SO GIVEN THE FINANCIAL AND LEGAL RESTRAINTS IT HAS TO WORK UNDER THE F. E. C. HAS BEEN SHOWING SIGNS OF SHEDDING ITS TOOTHLESS TIGER IMAGE </s>
<s> THE AVERAGE FINE AGAINST MEMBERS OF CONGRESS HAS GROWN BY FOUR HUNDRED PERCENT IN THE PAST TWO YEARS AND THE COMMISSION HASN'T BACKED AWAY FROM FIGHTS WITH PROMINENT MEMBERS </s>
<s> THIS SPRING THE F. E. C. SUED A POLITICAL ACTION COMMITTEE HEADED BY HOUSE REPUBLICAN WHIP NEWT GINGRICH THEN EARLIER THIS MONTH THE F. E. C. PASSED TOUGH NEW PROPOSED RULES ON HOW MEMBERS OF CONGRESS SPEND THEIR LEFTOVER CAMPAIGN FUNDS </s>
