<s> THIS LATEST DIPLOMATIC FAILURE HAS ONCE AGAIN RAISED SPECULATION ABOUT THE POSSIBILITY OF MILITARY ACTION </s>
<s> ROLF KNUTSEN THE SPECIAL U. N. ENVOY HAD ORIGINALLY BEEN DISPATCHED AS A RESULT OF PRESSURE BY LATIN AMERICAN NATIONS TO SEEK A DIPLOMATIC SOLUTION </s>
<s> IN AN EFFORT TO AVERT A POSSIBLE U. S. LED INVASION THESE COUNTRIES URGED THAT A HIGH LEVEL U. N. DELEGATION BE DISPATCHED TO MEET WITH HAITIAN STRONG MAN GENERAL RAOUL CEDRAS AND HIS ALLIES </s>
<s> THE DELEGATION'S MANDATE WAS TO PERSUADE CEDRAS AND HIS ASSOCIATES TO STEP DOWN AND LEAVE THE COUNTRY BUT BEFORE DISPATCHING THE DELEGATION SPECIAL ENVOY KNUTSEN WAS SENT TO THE DOMINICAN REPUBLIC LAST WEEK TO SEE IF THE HAITIAN MILITARY WOULD AGREE TO MEET WITH IT </s>
<s> THE U. N. WAS EAGER TO AVOID ANY KIND OF PUBLIC HUMILIATION BY THE HAITIAN MILITARY AND DID NOT WANT THE DELEGATION OF SENIOR U. N. OFFICIALS TO TRAVEL TO HAITI WITHOUT THE REGIME'S CONSENT </s>
<s> KNUTSEN DID MANAGE TO ESTABLISH CONTACT WITH THE MILITARY REGIME VIA INTERMEDIARIES IN THE DOMINICAN REPUBLIC BUT THE HAITIAN AUTHORITIES RULED OUT ANY TALKS THAT DEALT WITH THE DEPARTURE OF CEDRAS AND HIS ALLIES </s>
<s> SECRETARY GENERAL BOUTROS BOUTROS GHALI </s>
<s> THE MILITARY PEOPLE IN HAITI REFUSE TO DISCUSS WITH MY SPECIAL REPRESENTATIVE AND THUS I INFORM THE SECURITY COUNCIL THAT I WILL NOT CONTINUE THIS INITIATIVE UNLESS IN THE FUTURE ONE WILL RECEIVE THE MANDATE FROM THE SECURITY COUNCIL OR UNLESS THERE IS A DRASTIC CHANGE IN HAITI BUT FOR THE TIME BEING I THE MISSION HAVE NOT BEEN SUCCESSFUL </s>
<s> AFTER HEARING BOUTROS GHALI'S REPORT THERE WAS LITTLE THE SECURITY COUNCIL COULD DO </s>
<s> IT HAS ALREADY GRANTED AN AUTHORIZATION FOR NATIONS TO USE WHATEVER MEANS NECESSARY INCLUDING MILITARY FORCE TO OUST THE HAITIAN REGIME AND RESTORE PRESIDENT JEAN BERTRAND ARISTIDE AS CALLED FOR IN THE AGREEMENT SIGNED LAST JULY ON GOVERNOR'S ISLAND IN NEW YORK BUT WASHINGTON HAS YET TO DECIDE WHETHER OR NOT IT INTENDS TO USE FORCE TO RESTORE ARISTIDE TO POWER </s>
<s> DIPLOMATS SAY THAT IN THE ABSENCE OF A DECISION BY THE U. S. THERE IS LITTLE TO DO EXCEPT TO WAIT </s>
<s> AS A RESULT THE COUNCIL CHOSE TO ISSUE ANOTHER IN A LONG LINE OF STATEMENTS CRITICIZING THE REGIME </s>
<s> IT WAS READ BY COUNCIL PRESIDENT URI PERANSOV OF RUSSIA </s>
<s> THE MEMBERS OF THE SECURITY COUNCIL DEPLORE THE REJECTION BY THE LEGAL DE FACTO REGIME IN HAITI OF THE INITIATIVE CARRIED OUT UNDER THE INSTRUCTIONS OF THE SECRETARY GENERAL </s>
<s> ONCE AGAIN THE REGIME HAS DISCOUNTED THE POSSIBILITY OF PEACEFULLY IMPLEMENTING THE GOVERNORS ISLAND AGREEMENT </s>
<s> EVEN THOUGH WASHINGTON HAS YET TO DECIDE WHETHER TO INVADE THERE ARE CONTINUING SIGNALS IT MAY DO SO </s>
<s> IN KINGSTON JAMAICA THE U. S. AND A GROUP OF FOUR CARIBBEAN NATIONS WARNED HAITI'S MILITARY THEY ARE PREPARED TO USE ALL NECESSARY MEANS TO INSURE THAT CEDRAS AND HIS ALLIES DEPART </s>
<s> THEY ALSO ANNOUNCED THAT THEIR MILITARY FORCES WOULD BEGIN TRAINING IN PUERTO RICO FOR A POSSIBLE U. S. LED INVASION OF HAITI </s>
