<s> WELL I WOULDN'T SAY THAT VIETNAM HAS THAT STRAINED A RELATIONSHIP WITH THE U. S. ANYMORE AND A LOT OF THE COUNTRIES WE GO TO DON'T HAVE STRAINED RELATIONS WITH THE U. S. I MEAN INDIA OR SENEGAL </s>
<s> WE PICK PLACES BECAUSE WE THINK THERE ARE CERTAIN INTERESTING POLITICAL AND ECONOMIC ISSUES THAT ARE GOING ON IN THEM THAT U. S. PEOPLE SHOULD KNOW MORE ABOUT </s>
<s> IN THE CASE OF CUBA WE THOUGHT WE'D BE DOING ONE OR TWO TRIPS A YEAR TO CUBA AND WE FOUND THAT THERE WAS SO MUCH INTEREST PARTLY BECAUSE YOU CAN'T GO THERE ON YOUR OWN </s>
<s> YOU REALLY HAVE TO GO THROUGH A GROUP LIKE OURS BECAUSE OF THE U. S. REGULATIONS THAT WE FIND WE CAN'T KEEP UP WITH THE INTEREST THERE IS IN SEEING CUBA </s>
