<s> AND THE OTHER THING THAT WE REALIZED WHEN WE STARTED TAKING GROUPS UNDER THE RESTRICTIONS THAT EXISTED AND THAT WAS THAT THE PEOPLE HAD TO BE PROFESSIONAL RESEARCHERS OR THEY HAD TO BE NEWS GATHERERS OR JOURNALISTS </s>
<s> WE REALIZED WHEN WE STARTED TAKING GROUPS IN THOSE CATEGORIES THAT WE SAW HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF CANADIANS AND MEXICANS AND ITALIANS AND GERMANS AND ALL THESE OTHER PEOPLE WHO WERE THERE JUST TO LIE ON THE BEACH OR DO WHATEVER THEY WANTED TO DO AND THEY HAD NO RESTRICTIONS TO GO TO CUBA </s>
<s> SO WE STARTED TO SEE THAT THE POLICY DIDN'T REALLY MAKE ANY SENSE </s>
<s> WE SAID IF WE CAN GO TO VIETNAM IF WE CAN GO TO CHINA IF WE CAN GO TO ANY OTHER COMMUNIST COUNTRY WHY CAN'T WE GO TO CUBA </s>
<s> AND HOW COME ALL THESE OTHER PEOPLE FROM ALL THE REST OF THE WORLD CAN GO THERE </s>
<s> SO WE JOINED WITH SOME OTHER ORGANIZATIONS AROUND THE COUNTRY AND CREATED THE FREEDOM TO TRAVEL CAMPAIGN TO CHALLENGE THE U. S. GOVERNMENT'S POLICIES ON RESTRICTING U. S. TRAVEL TO CUBA AND THAT TURNED INTO MUSHROOMED INTO JUST A HUGE CONTROVERSY PITTING US AGAINST THE U. S. GOVERNMENT </s>
<s> AND THE GOVERNMENTS EVENTUALLY CLAMPED DOWN I MEAN TRIED TO STOP THE TRIP IN EFFECT </s>
