<s> INFORMATION IS WHAT REPORTERS WANT MOST TO GET ABOUT THE O. J. SIMPSON CASE AND WHAT THE JUDGE PRESIDING OVER THE TRIAL WOULD LIKE TO CONTROL </s>
<s> A GAG ORDER IS HOW JUDGE LANCE ITO WANTS TO ACCOMPLISH THIS WOULD PRESCRIBE WHAT LAWYERS AND OTHERS INVOLVED CAN SAY PUBLICLY ABOUT THE CASE BUT SOME CONSTITUTIONAL EXPERTS SAY JUDGE ITO MAY HAVE GONE MUCH TOO FAR SCOPING A GAG ORDER THAT MAY BE UNPRECEDENTED IN SCOPE AND THEY SAY TURNING FIRST AMENDMENT LAW UPSIDE DOWN </s>
<s> WHILE JUDGES OFTEN TRY TO GAG LAWYERS FROM SPEAKING JUDGE ITO GOES MUCH FURTHER </s>
<s> HE WANTS ALL MOTIONS FILED WITH THE COURT TO BE UNDER SEAL </s>
<s> SAYING EVERYTHING FILED WITH THE COURT WON'T BE SEEN BY THE PUBLIC AND BY THE PRESS IS ABSOLUTELY UNCONSTITUTIONAL </s>
<s> IT IS AN ATTEMPT TO REGULATE NOT THE ATTORNEYS IN THE CASE BUT TO REGULATE THE PRESS AND TO REGULATE THE MOST FUNDAMENTAL FREEDOM THE RIGHT OF FREEDOM OF SPEECH </s>
<s> WHEN ALL ELSE FAILS TO STOP UNWANTED LEAKS OF INFORMATION TO THE MEDIA JUDGES OFTEN RESORT TO GAG ORDERS </s>
