<s> LATER THAT YEAR THE I. R. A. DECLARED ITS FIRST TRUCE ON JUNE TWENTY SIXTH </s>
<s> IT FELL APART ON JULY NINTH </s>
<s> THE NEXT CEASE FIRE CAME ON DECEMBER TWENTY SECOND NINETEEN SEVENTY FOUR WHEN THE I. R. A. DECLARED WHAT IT CALLED A TEMPORARY CESSATION OF ITS ACTIVITIES </s>
<s> IT LASTED NEARLY A MONTH </s>
<s> AND IN EARLY FEBRUARY OF NINETEEN SEVENTY FIVE THE I. R. A. CALLED AN INDEFINITE TRUCE BUT BY THE SUMMER OF NINETEEN SEVENTY FIVE THE TRUCE HAD COLLAPSED </s>
<s> ALL OF THE CEASE FIRES WERE DESTROYED BY DISAGREEMENT BETWEEN THE PARTIES INVOLVED AND LOYALIST VIOLENCE IN THE NORTH </s>
<s> WITH THE LAST TRUCE IN RUINS THE I. R. A. PUT NEW PRESSURE ON BRITAIN TO PULL OUT OF NORTHERN IRELAND </s>
<s> IT AIMED STRAIGHT AT THE HEART OF BRITISH LIFE AND GOVERNMENT AND IT SUCCEEDED IN NINETEEN EIGHTY THREE WITH A BOMB AT HARRODS'S LONDON'S LANDMARK DEPARTMENT STORE </s>
<s> A YEAR LATER THE I. R. A. SHOWED JUST HOW FAR IT COULD REACH </s>
<s> IT BLEW UP A HOTEL HOSTING A CONFERENCE BY PRIME MINISTER MARGARET THATCHER'S CONSERVATIVE PARTY </s>
<s> BUT THE I. R. A.'S BOMBING CAMPAIGN BEGAN TO WORK AGAINST IT </s>
<s> AN EXPLOSION IN NINETEEN EIGHTY SEVEN IN THE TOWN OF ENNISKILLEN IN NORTHERN IRELAND KILLED ELEVEN PEOPLE AT A MEMORIAL SERVICE AND INJURED SIXTY THREE </s>
<s> EVEN MANY OF THE I. R. A.'S SUPPORTERS WERE DISGUSTED </s>
<s> AFTER ENNISKILLEN THE GROUP SHIFTED ITS FOCUS </s>
<s> IT SET OUT TO DAMAGE THE BRITISH ECONOMY </s>
<s> THE I. R. A. LAUNCHED A SPECTACULAR ATTACK ON LONDON'S FINANCIAL DISTRICT IN APRIL OF NINETEEN NINETY TWO </s>
<s> TWO BOMBS RIPPED THROUGH THE BALTIC EXCHANGE BUILDING CAUSING HUNDREDS OF MILLIONS OF DOLLARS IN DAMAGE </s>
<s> BUT THE ECONOMY WAS NOT THE I. R. A.'S ONLY TARGET </s>
<s> ALMOST A YEAR LATER AT WARRINGTON IN NINETEEN NINETY THREE A BOMBING KILLED A THREE YEAR OLD BOY </s>
<s> ONCE AGAIN EVEN THOSE DEVOTED TO THE I. R. A.'S CAUSE QUESTIONED ITS TECHNIQUES </s>
<s> A YEAR AGO SINN FEIN LEADER JERRY ADAMS AND THE MODERATE CATHOLIC POLITICIAN JOHN HUME OFFERED A PEACE PROPOSAL </s>
<s> ONE MONTH LATER IN OCTOBER NINETEEN NINETY THREE AN I. R. A. IN BELFAST KILLED TEN PEOPLE </s>
<s> JERRY ADAMS CALLED IT A DEVASTATING TRAGEDY. THE BRITISH GOVERNMENT ATTACKED ADAMS FOR TALKING PEACE WHILE THE I. R. A. WAGED WAR AND IT REJECTED THE HUME ADAMS PROPOSAL </s>
<s> BUT AT THE END OF LAST YEAR BRITAIN AND IRELAND CAME FORWARD WITH A PROPOSAL OF THEIR OWN </s>
<s> THE DOWNING STREET DECLARATION OFFERED THE I. R. A. A ROLE IN PEACE TALKS IF THEY MET ONE CONDITION </s>
<s> IF THE PROVISIONALS WILL END AND RENOUNCE VIOLENCE FOR GOOD THE BRITISH GOVERNMENT IS PREPARED TO ENTER INTO PRELIMINARY EXPLORATORY DIALOGUE WITH SINN FEIN WITHIN THREE MONTHS WHEN CESSATION OF VIOLENCE HAS BEEN CLEARLY ESTABLISHED </s>
<s> THE BRITISH WANTED THE I. R. A. TO END THEIR FIGHT FOR GOOD </s>
<s> THE I. R. A. AGREED AND THE COMING MONTHS WILL TEST EVERYONE'S COMMITMENT TO PEACE </s>
