<s> ON THE FIRST OF SEPTEMBER IN ONE THOUSAND EIGHT HUNDRED NINETY FOUR THE RESIDENTS OF HINCKLEY MINNESOTA THOUGHT THEY WERE WATCHING THE END OF THE WORLD </s>
<s> THEIR TOWN AND SEVERAL SURROUNDING VILLAGES DISAPPEARED IN A FIRE STORM WHICH KILLED HUNDREDS OF PEOPLE AND INCINERATED A QUARTER OF A MILLION ACRES IN JUST FOUR HOURS </s>
<s> IT WAS ONE OF THIS COUNTRY'S DEADLIEST FOREST FIRES AND MADE NEWSPAPER FRONT PAGES AROUND THE WORLD </s>
<s> THIS WEEK THE PEOPLE OF HINCKLEY WILL COMMEMORATE THE EVENT AND THE LESSONS LEARNED ON THAT LATE SUMMER'S DAY </s>
<s> MINNESOTA PUBLIC RADIO'S EUAN KERR REPORTS </s>
<s> TO MANY TRAVELING THROUGH MINNESOTA NOWADAYS HINCKLEY IS JUST THE PLACE WHERE YOU STOP MIDWAY BETWEEN THE TWIN CITIES AND DULUTH TO GRAB A CUP OF COFFEE AND A SWEET ROLL </s>
<s> THERE ARE OFTEN LINES OF CARS STRETCHING BACK ON TO THE INTERSTATE HEADING FOR THE RESTAURANTS OR PERHAPS THE NEARBY CASINO </s>
<s> JUST A MILE OR SO TO THE WEST THE TRAFFIC IS THINNER AND HINCKLEY'S MAIN DRAG IS MUCH QUIETER </s>
<s> THE PEACEFUL SOUNDS OF SUMMER MAKE IT HARD TO IMAGINE THIS BEING A PLACE OF HORROR AND DEATH BUT IT WAS </s>
<s> EVEN TODAY WHEN YOU DIG INTO THE EARTH AROUND HINCKLEY IT'S INTERESTING TO SEE WHERE THE FIRE LINE ACTUALLY WAS </s>
<s> IT'S ABOUT A FOOT UNDERGROUND BUT IT'S STILL THERE </s>
<s> JEANNIE COFFEE IS THE DIRECTOR OF THE HINCKLEY FIRE MUSEUM WHICH IS HOUSED IN THE TOWN'S FORMER TRAIN DEPOT </s>
<s> SHE SAYS ONE HUNDRED YEARS AGO FIRE WAS JUST A FACT OF LIFE OF HINCKLEY </s>
<s> THE TOWN WAS A LOGGING CENTER AND THE LUMBER COMPANIES RAN SLOPPY OPERATIONS </s>
<s> FOR TWENTY YEARS THEY CLEAR CUT THROUGH THE REGION LEAVING SLASH PILES HUGE MOUNDS OF BRANCHES AND WASTE TIMBER LITTERING THE AREA </s>
<s> WAIST HIGH STUMPS FROM TREES CUT AT THE SNOW LINE IN THE DEAD OF WINTER STUDDED THE GROUND </s>
<s> FIRES WERE SO RUN OF THE MILL RESIDENTS JUST ACCEPTED THE COMMON RESPIRATORY PROBLEMS CAUSED BY SMOKE ONE THOUSAND EIGHT HUNDRED NINETY FOUR SEEMED PARTICULARLY BAD </s>
<s> THEY'D HAD LESS THAN TWO INCHES OF RAIN FROM MAY UNTIL SEPTEMBER FIRST WHEN THE FIRE HAPPENED AND SO WHEN THE FIRE HAPPENED PEOPLE JUST THOUGHT IT WAS ANOTHER FIRE </s>
<s> ON SEPTEMBER FIRST HINCKLEY EXPERIENCED A TEMPERATURE INVERSION AS A BLANKET OF COOLER AIR TRAPPED THE WARMER AIR BENEATH </s>
<s> THERE IS DISAGREEMENT AS TO HOW IT ALL STARTED BUT SOMEHOW TWO FIRES GOT OUT OF CONTROL AND THEIR HEAT AND SMOKE WERE TRAPPED UNDER THE INVERSION </s>
<s> EVENTUALLY THE FIRES MERGED AND THE RESULTING BLAZE WAS FIERCE ENOUGH TO PUNCH A HOLE A THROUGH THE BLANKET OF COOLER AIR </s>
<s> AS THE HOT AIR BLASTED UPWARDS SURROUNDING AIR RUSHED IN TO TAKE ITS PLACE FANNING THE FLAMES AND INTENSIFYING THE BLAZE </s>
<s> JEANNIE COFFEE SAYS SUDDENLY THE PEOPLE OF HINCKLEY WERE NOT FACING A FIRE THEY WERE FACING A FIRE STORM NOT UNLIKE THOSE FOLLOWING THE BOMBING OF HIROSHIMA AND NAGASAKI </s>
<s> IT ENTERED THE TOWN HERE IN HINCKLEY ABOUT FOUR </s>
<s> THAT WAS WHEN IT WAS ON THE EDGE OF TOWN AND IT DIDN'T TAKE LONG TO DESTROY THE TOWN </s>
<s> I MEAN JUST MINUTES </s>
<s> THE HINCKLEY FIRE STORM ROSE FIVE MILES IN THE AIR AND THE GLOW FROM THE FLAMES WAS SEEN TWO HUNDRED MILES AWAY IN MASON CITY IOWA </s>
<s> THE RESIDENTS OF HINCKLEY TRIED TO FLEE MANY OF THEM HEADING FOR THE RAIL DEPOT HOPING TO TAKE A TRAIN OUT OF TOWN </s>
<s> AS THEY CROWDED IN THE DEPOT'S ROOF BURST INTO FLAMES FORCING PEOPLE BACK OUT INTO THE HEAT THE SMOKE AND THE WIND HEADING FOR THE TOWN'S OTHER DEPOT </s>
<s> IDA BILLINGS WAS THERE HER FAMILY </s>
<s> HER WRITTEN ACCOUNT NOW IN THE MUSEUM MAKES HORRIFYING READING </s>
<s> IN THE HURRY AND SCURRY I BECAME SEPARATED FROM MY FAMILY </s>
<s> THE HIGH WIND TOOK ME BLOCKS OUT OF MY WAY TO THE DEPOT WHERE MY FAMILY WENT </s>
<s> AT TIMES MY FEET DID NOT TOUCH GROUND DUE TO THE HIGH WIND </s>
<s> I WAS TOSSED HERE AND THERE </s>
<s> ONCE I SAW A TEAM OF HORSES WITH SIX BARRELS IN THE WAGON </s>
<s> THEY CROSSED THE BRIDGE GOING NORTH </s>
<s> MANY PEOPLE ON FOOT WERE CROSSING THE SAME BRIDGE </s>
<s> I TOO FELT LIKE GOING THAT WAY BUT ON SECOND THOUGHT KNEW IT WOULD NOT TAKE ME TO THE EM DEPOT </s>
<s> IF I HAD GONE I WITH ABOUT TWO HUNDRED OTHERS WOULD HAVE PERISHED IN THAT SWAMP NORTH OF TOWN WHERE THEY SOUGHT SHELTER </s>
<s> IN FACT ONE HUNDRED TWENTY SEVEN PEOPLE DIED OF ASPHYXIATION IN THE SWAMP </s>
<s> THREE TRAINS MADE IT THROUGH THE INFERNO TO PICK UP SOME OF THE PANICKED RESIDENTS </s>
<s> TWO OF THE TRAINS LINKED UP AND LOADED OVER FIVE HUNDRED PEOPLE BEFORE BACKING ALL THE WAY NORTH TO SAFETY IN DULUTH </s>
<s> MARY COVED ANOTHER YOUNG GIRL WHO LIVED THROUGH THE FIRE TO PASS ON HER ACCOUNT WAS ON THE TRAIN </s>
<s> NOT EVERYONE WAS SO LUCKY </s>
<s> WE WERE ALL SO THANKFUL TO GET ON THIS TRAIN AND MOVE AWAY FROM THIS TERRIBLE BLACKNESS AND FIRE ROARING LIKE A CYCLONE IN THE AIR </s>
<s> AS WE RODE ALONG THE GNRR TRACKS WE SAW SOME MEN WOMEN AND CHILDREN RUNNING ALONG THE SIDE OF THE TRACK WITH OUTSTRETCHED ARMS </s>
<s> SUDDENLY THEY WERE LOST SIGHT OF IN THE FLAMES </s>
<s> IT WAS A TERRIBLE SIGHT THAT WOULD SICKEN AND APPALL THE STRONGEST OF MEN </s>
<s> ANOTHER TRAIN WITH ENGINEER JIM ROOT AT THE THROTTLE ALSO BEGAN PULLING OUT </s>
<s> THE TRAIN WAS ON FIRE THE WINDOWS BURSTING DUE TO THE INTENSE HEAT </s>
<s> THE TRAIN ONLY MADE IT TO SKUNK LAKE JUST NORTH OF TOWN WHERE IT WAS STOPPED BY FIRE </s>
<s> THE CREW HERDED THE PEOPLE OFF THE CARRIAGES AND INTO THE WATER WHERE THEY LAY FOR HOURS BADLY BURNED BUT ALIVE UNTIL THE FIRE HAD PASSED </s>
<s> PEOPLE HUDDLED UNDER BLANKETS AND FINE LINENS SOAKED IN THE SWAMPY WATER TO WARD OFF THE SMOKE AND CINDERS </s>
<s> THEY HAD BEEN GRABBED BECAUSE THEY WERE HEIRLOOMS BUT BECAME LIFESAVERS </s>
<s> THE OFFICIAL DEATH TOLL WAS FOUR HUNDRED EIGHTEEN ALTHOUGH THIS NUMBER DOES NOT INCLUDE ANY OF THE NATIVE AMERICANS WHO DIED NOR THE MANY WHO WERE TO DIE OVER THE COMING YEAR FROM THE LINGERING EFFECTS OF BURNS AND SMOKE INHALATION </s>
<s> THE REAL TOTAL WAS CLOSER TO SIX HUNDRED </s>
<s> AND THIS STORY THIS IS THE STORY THAT MY MOTHER WROTE ABOUT THE HINCKLEY FIRE </s>
<s> EDNA SHOBER IS SITTING IN THE FRONT ROOM OF HER HOUSE JUST A FEW YARDS FROM THE MUSEUM LOOKING AT A THICK FAMILY HISTORY BOOK PUT TOGETHER BY HER BROTHER </s>
<s> HER GRANDPARENTS MOVED TO HINCKLEY FROM SWEDEN IN ONE THOUSAND EIGHT HUNDRED EIGHTY SEVEN </s>
<s> SHOBER SAYS HER PREGNANT GRANDMOTHER SAVED THE FAMILY INCLUDING EDNA'S MOTHER BY MAKING THEM SHELTER IN THEIR WELL AT THE FARMHOUSE COVERED WITH WET BLANKETS </s>
<s> WHEN THEY CAME OUT THEY SAW THEIR FARM WAS GONE </s>
<s> WHEN THE FIRE WAS OVER THEN THEY WALKED TO THE RAILROAD AND THEY WHEN THEY GOT TO THE MY AUNT WHO IS OLDER THAN MY MOTHER LOOKED BACK AND SHE THOUGHT SHE SAW A DOG OR SOMETHING LAYING AGAINST THE TRACKS </s>
<s> WELL THEY WENT BACK TO SEE AND IT WAS A MR. LARSON WHO LATER BECAME MY UNCLE AND HE HAD DUG HIS FACE DOWN INTO THE GROUND NEAR THE TREES TO GET SOME AIR TO BREATHE </s>
<s> WELL HE WAS UNCONSCIOUS SO THEY CARRIED HIM UP TO HINCKLEY </s>
<s> BUT HINCKLEY WAS GONE </s>
<s> TO THE NORTH THE TOWN OF SANDSTONE WAS ALSO GONE AS WERE FOUR SMALLER COMMUNITIES </s>
<s> BUT SOON THE TOWNS WERE BACK FOR WHILE THE STORY OF THE FIRE IS AMAZING SO IS THE STORY OF THE RECOVERY </s>
<s> HINCKLEY WAS REBUILT BEFORE WINTER </s>
<s> DESPITE THE HORROR AND DEVASTATION SOME SAW THE HINCKLEY FIRE AS A BLESSING IN DISGUISE </s>
<s> THE LOGGERS HAD BEEN ON THE POINT OF MOVING OUT AND JEANNIE COFFEE SAYS THE WAY THE FIRE BURNED OUT THE STUMPS GAVE LOCAL FARMERS A HUGE BOOST </s>
<s> THE FIRST NEWSPAPER AFTER THE FIRE THE HEADLINE WAS FIFTEEN YEARS WORK IN FIFTEEN MINUTES </s>
<s> YEA YOU KNOW THIS IS WHAT A FIRE CAN DO AND IT SAVED THEM A PILE OF WORK AND BECAME A REAL AGRICULTURAL COMMUNITY </s>
<s> AND THERE WERE LESSONS FOR THE LOGGERS TOO </s>
<s> MINNESOTA DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES COMMISSIONER ROD SANDO HAS LONG STUDIED FIRES AND THEIR EFFECTS </s>
