<s> A SMALL HIGHLY EXPERIMENTAL STUDY MAY PROMISE RELIEF SOME DAY FOR PATIENTS WITH THE OFTEN FATAL LUNG DISEASE CYSTIC FIBROSIS </s>
<s> IN OUR NEWS FROM MEDICINE REPORT AL HINMAN LOOKS AT HOW GENE THERAPY COULD LEAD TO BETTER TREATMENT AND POSSIBLE EVEN A CURE FOR C. F. </s>
<s> LEE ANNE RITTENBAUM HAS CYSTIC FIBROSIS </s>
<s> FREQUENT MEDICAL CHECK UPS ARE A WAY OF LIFE FOR THIS NINE YEAR OLD </s>
<s> CYSTIC FIBROSIS IS THE MOST COMMON FATAL HEREDITARY DISEASE IN THE UNITED STATES </s>
<s> THEY BECOME INFECTED INFLAMED AND THERE'S THICK STICKY MUCUS AND THE LUNGS GET CLOGGED UP </s>
<s> TO KEEP PATIENTS BREATHING AND ALIVE INTO ADULTHOOD DOCTORS PRESCRIBED DAILY LUNG CLEARING THERAPY AND LOTS OF DRUGS </s>
